shrug /ʃrʌɡ/

(shrugging,shrugged,shrugs) 

1. V-T/V-I If you shrug , you raise your shoulders to show that you are not interested in something or that you do not know or care about something. 耸肩 

例： I shrugged, as if to say, 'Why not?' 我耸了耸肩，好像在说,“为什么不？” 

2. N-COUNT Shrug is also a noun. 耸肩 

例： 'I suppose so,' said Anna with a shrug. “我想是这样，”安娜耸耸肩说道。

